197
00:07:57,380 --> 00:08:01,000
an imaginary lattice of meter sticks,

198
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,500
so that every point in

199
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,000
space is labeled by a X,

200
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:10,940
a Y, and a Z, a set of meter sticks,

201
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:15,100
and at each vertex of the lattice, a clock.

202
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:18,500
And the clock measures time.

203
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:22,320
Now, in Newtonian physics, in Newtonian physics,

204
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:27,320
Newton imagined that time was very, very universal.

205
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,560
